conbody.p:
Press the Quiz settings button to open a Quiz settings window ( ) where you can change settings common for the whole quiz:


quiz description;

course;

quiz author;

maximum grade;

quiz time limit in minutes;

enforce the order of questions so that the students can not go back and change their answers;

randomize question order;

allow the students to see their results after they complete the test;

allow instant correction (students can instantly see correctness of their answers and make another attempt).

You can specify the following parameters for each question individually in the question settings panel ( ):


question title;

optional time limit in seconds (can not exceed total limit for the quiz (?) _fixme_);

question weight for overall quiz score;

oral answer option (recorded from student microphone).

You can use several types of question on the quiz:


multiple choice;

multiple answer (?) _fixme_;

fill in the blank spaces;

relations (matching items);

sequence order;

hot spot;

drag and drop;

open question;

dummy question (does not require students to give an answer and can be used to convey some of information).
